Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Cut tops off bell peppers; discard seeds and membranes. Cook peppers in boiling water 5 minutes; drain. Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add shallots; saute 3 minutes or until tender. Add mushrooms, and saute 4 minutes or until tender. Add parsley, almonds, sherry, and chile powder; saute 3 minutes. Add rice, juice, black pepper, garlic powder, and salt; saute 3 minutes. Spoon 3/4 cup rice mixture into each bell pepper; top each with 1 tablespoon cheese. Place peppers in a 13 x 9â€“inch baking dish; bake at 350 degrees F for 15 minutes.